==English==

===Etymology===
A portmanteau word from Afrikaans ''sout'' meaning salt + ''piel'' meaning penis. See definition below.

===Noun===
'''soutpiel'''

# {{italbrac|South African|vulgar|army slang}} An English speaking South African.  So named for having one foot in South Africa, one foot in England and his penis dangling in the Atlantic.

===Derived terms===
* [[Soutie]].

